      <hedline>
        <hl1>SPIKE IN BRAZIL INFLATION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Inflation rate in Brazil reached five-year high in July; benchmark inflation index rose 1.61 percent, compared with 0.23 percent in June (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The inflation rate in Brazil reached a five-year high in July, reflecting government price increases in gasoline, electricity and telephone service. The government's benchmark inflation index rose 1.61 percent last month, compared with an increase of 0.23 percent in June. In the last 12 months, inflation totaled 7.1 percent, higher than Brazil's target of 6 percent for 2000.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
